An unidentified male has been gunned down on Hans Schoeman Street in Strijdom Park, Randburg, this afternoon, reports the Randburg Sun.
According to an eyewitness, police and paramedics found the man’s lifeless body on the driver’s seat of his vehicle and nothing appeared to have been stolen.
The man sustained multiple injuries on his neck and chest area and was pronounced dead on the scene.
Details surrounding his death are sketchy at present.
This is a developing story. Head to the Randburg Sun for more.